       "id": 5146996093616128,
       "name": "CSS Symbols()",
       "summary": "CSS symbols() is a CSS function that enables CSS counter styles inline as a value of properties such as list-style. This enables a simpler way to define a counter style compared to using @counter-style.",
-      "motivation": null,
+      "motivation": "Defining a custom list marker in CSS today requires authoring a named  @counter-style  rule and referencing it by name, which is needlessly verbose for one-off, anonymous markers. The  symbols()  function lets authors define the same counter style inline, without inventing or managing a global name. It works wherever a counter style is accepted, including  list-style-type  and the  counter() / counters()  functions. Firefox has shipped  symbols()  since 2015, but Chromium and Safari have not, leaving a standing interoperability gap that web developers regularly encounter (https://issues.chromium.org/issues/484510686).",
       "url": "https://chromestatus.com/feature/5146996093616128",
